      "term": "Momentum Investing",
      "explanation_en": "Momentum investing means buying stocks that have been rising and showing strong technical signals \u2014 like RSI in the bullish zone and MACD crossovers \u2014 on the bet that recent strength will continue. It works because trends tend to persist in the short term as more buyers pile in. The risk is that momentum can reverse sharply, which is why stop-losses and watching for overbought RSI (above 70) are important guardrails.",
